The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as 1:20 p.m. in  Lima  trading.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.8 percent to 22,726.12,
extending its drop in April to 3.8 percent. The MSCI All Peru
Capped Index slid 0.8 percent to 2,955.72 today.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, plunged 9 percent
to 81 cents after an agreement for land rights for its Canariaco
copper deposit was delayed.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 2.1 percent to $41.35 after
Chief Executive Officer Roque Benavides today said costs will
rise at its Minas Conga gold project.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., dropped 1 percent to 2.93 soles. The shares
slid as U.S. stocks slumped, according to Jorge Rodriguez, an
analyst at Lima-based brokerage Kallpa Securities SAB.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of
Gerdau SA known as Siderperu, slid 1 percent to 98 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
